UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. CHANG CHOW, Appellee. No. 8515. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. April 12, 1937. Ingram M. Stainback, U. S. Atty., of Honolulu, T. H. Ebert J. Botts, of Honolulu, T. H., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of appellant, consented to by appellee, ordered appeal dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court herein issued forthwith.
